# Simple-Chatbot-SISA--Project
SISA is a terminal-based AI chatbot built in Python that combines the power of Google Gemini AI and Google Custom Search API to provide intelligent, real-time responses. It works entirely from the command line with support for both Linux/macOS , offering color-coded feedback, smart phrase detection, and dynamic search capabilities.
# ðŸ¤– Simple Chatbot (SISA) â€” Linux/macOS Version

This version of the chatbot is designed to run on any **Linux** or **macOS** terminal, with rich colored output and full functionality using Google Gemini and Custom Search APIs.

---

## âœ… Requirements

- Python 3.8 or higher
- Internet connection
- Google Gemini API key
- Google Programmable Search API key

---

## ðŸ“¦ Installation Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/isayani-78/simple-chatbot(SISA)-project.git
cd simple-chatbot-project/Simple_chatbot(SISA)_linux_version
```

---

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
python3 setup.py
```

This installs all required packages as listed in `settings.json`.

---

### 3. Set Up API Keys

Open `settings.json` and add your API keys:

```json
"credentials": {
  "gemini": {
    "api-key": "your_gemini_api_key",
    "model-name": "gemini-pro"
  },
  "g-search": {
    "api-key": "your_google_search_api_key",
    "id": "your_custom_search_engine_id"
  }
}
```

---

## ðŸ’¬ Run the Chatbot

```bash
python3 main.py
```

Example interactions:

```bash
ðŸ¤– Ask me anything...
search best Linux distros
help
exit
```

